==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''genos'' 'race' + [[-cide]].

===Noun===
'''genocide'''
# The systematic killing of an entire ethnic group, nation, or political group.
# Killing in whole or in part a distinctive group of people on the basis of race, caste, colour, sex, language, religion, political or other opinion, national or social origin, property or place of birth etc.
#Genocide .. is the mass killing of substantial numbers of human beings, when not in the course of military forces of an avowed enemy, under conditions of the essential defenselessness and helplessness of the victims". (Israel W. Charny in ''Genocide: Conceptual and Historical Dimensions ed. George Andreopoulos, 1994'').

